## 3. Organization Facet:

### 3.1 Roles and Responsibilities:

    ☐ Map Win Stakeholders (Dim 2 functional archetypes) to organizational roles
        - Dim 2 defines "the product's commercial success requires a Pre-Sales Engineer role"
        - Operating Model defines "we have 3 Pre-Sales Engineers in LATAM, reporting to VP Sales"
        - See FAQ Q29
    ☐ Define organizational roles for each Work Model track owner:
        - Discovery: Product Manager, UX Researcher, Executive Leadership
        - Build: Tech Lead, Developers, QA
        - Run: DevOps, SRE
        - Win: Customer Success, Product Marketing, Sales, Support
        - Evolve: Process Leads, Product Ops, Engineering Managers
    ☐ Define RACI or equivalent for cross-track work (especially Customer Release lifecycle)
    ☐ Define who owns the Operational lever (internal process, tooling, automation, hiring) — this lever maps to Operating Model, not a specific track

### 3.2 Team Structures:

    ☐ Define team structure patterns (cross-functional squads, functional teams, matrix)
    ☐ Address how one person may cover multiple Win Stakeholder roles (startup scenario) vs. specialized roles (enterprise scenario)
    ☐ Define team composition guidance for each track

### 3.3 Skills and Training:

    ☐ Define PM skill profiles — what competencies are needed for Definition Model management
    ☐ Define skill profiles for each track's primary owner role
    ☐ Define training programs and certification (distinct from customer-facing education in Win Track)
    ☐ Define onboarding guidance for new team members per track

### 3.4 Tools and Resources:

    ☐ Define tooling standards (project management, artifact repositories, monitoring dashboards)
    ☐ Define resource allocation patterns per track

