## 4. Guidance Content (Playbooks and Procedures)

The Work Model defines the *structure* of guidance (what a playbook should cover). The Operating Model owns the *content* — actual procedures, templates, and methodology. Each work entity file has a `## Guidance Reference` section pointing to Operating Model playbooks.

### 4.1 Discovery Track Playbooks:

    ☐ Signal Exploration playbook (triggers, activities, decision points, pitfalls)
    ☐ Deliberation playbook (preparation, facilitation, decision recording)
    ☐ Research Task playbook (methodology selection, bias management, evidence standards)
    ☐ Experiment playbook (hypothesis framing, sample sizing, pass/fail criteria)
    ☐ Specification Task playbook (cross-dimensional review process, PSD quality checklist)
    ☐ Modeling Task playbook (entity creation workflow, relationship validation, FAQ updates)
    ☐ Prioritization playbook (scoring methodology, association criteria, trade-off frameworks)

### 4.2 Build Track Playbooks:

    ☐ Release Planning playbook
    ☐ Iteration Planning playbook
    ☐ Code review guidelines
    ☐ Quality gate definitions and enforcement procedures
    ☐ Bug triage and resolution workflow

### 4.3 Run Track Playbooks:

    ☐ Deployment runbook template and authoring guidelines
    ☐ Incident management playbook (severity classification, escalation, post-mortem process)
    ☐ Change management playbook (approval workflow, risk assessment, rollback procedures)
    ☐ Capacity planning playbook

### 4.4 Win Track Playbooks:

    ☐ GTM launch playbook
    ☐ Sales enablement asset creation guidelines
    ☐ Onboarding/Implementation playbook template
    ☐ QBR preparation and execution playbook
    ☐ Win/Loss analysis playbook
    ☐ Win Case resolution playbook (per type: Query, Service Request, Complaint, Escalation)
    ☐ Partner engagement playbook
    ☐ Revenue operations playbook
    ☐ Competitive battlecard creation and maintenance guidelines

### 4.5 Evolve Track Playbooks:

    ☐ Evolve Planning playbook (cycle scoping, prioritization of process improvements)
    ☐ Evolve Review playbook (per type: Process Effectiveness, Artifact Quality, Guidance Adequacy, Cross-Track Handoff)
    ☐ Evolve Definition Task playbook (entity authoring, assessment criteria design, DoD design)

### 4.6 Cross-Track Guidance:  

    ☐ Customer Release lifecycle coordination playbook (Discovery → Build → Run → Win)
    ☐ Feedback → Signal promotion criteria and workflow
    ☐ PSD → Build handoff checklist and quality expectations
    ☐ Evolve Findings → Definition Task conversion workflow

